<span id="freeTextContainer17944942336915865034">[4.5] <i>Butcher&apos;s Crossing</i> doesn&apos;t have much in common with Williams&apos; <i>Stoner</i> except for brilliant writing. The novel encapsulates the late 19th century U.S., on the brink of change, like nothing I&apos;ve ever read. At its core is the adventures of four men who embark on an arduous hunt for buffalo. Nothing works out as planned. There is carnage and futility and tragedy. A staggering, stunning work of literature.</span>
  <span id="freeText17944942336915865034" style="display:none">[4.5] <i>Butcher's Crossing</i> doesn't have much in common with Williams' <i>Stoner</i> except for brilliant writing. The novel encapsulates the late 19th century U.S., on the brink of change, like nothing I've ever read. At its core is the adventures of four men who embark on an arduous hunt for buffalo. Nothing works out as planned. There is carnage and futility and tragedy. A staggering, stunning work of literature.</span>
